---
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Aluminium Ingots for Construction & Architecture | Egypt Alumin" lang="en">
  <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
    <div class="container"><ol>
      <li><a href="/en/">Home</a></li>
      <li><a href="/en/industries/">Industries</a></li>
      <li aria-current="page">Construction</li>
    </ol></div>
  </nav>

  <section class="product-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="product-hero-grid" style="grid-template-columns:1fr;">
        <div style="max-width:800px;">
          <span class="eyebrow on-dark">Industry Application</span>
          <h1>Aluminium for Construction & Architecture</h1>
          <p class="product-hero-lead">Primary ingots for extrusion billets and architectural castings. Superior surface quality for anodising and powder coating applications.</p>
          <div class="product-hero-ctas">
            <a href="/en/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Request Specifications</a>
            <a href="/en/products/" class="btn btn-secondary">View All Products</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding:5rem 0;background:var(--warm-white);">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px;">
      <h2>Products for construction applications</h2>
      <p>Curtain wall systems, window and door profiles, structural facades, and decorative panels all begin with high-quality aluminium charge material. Consistent ingot chemistry is critical for predictable extrusion press performance and surface finish quality.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>A7 Primary Aluminium Ingot (EN 576)</strong> — The standard charge material for 6xxx series extrusion billets. Minimal iron and silicon for maximum anodising brightness and corrosion resistance in architectural applications.</li>
        <li><strong>AL-Si Alloy Ingot (EN 1706)</strong> — Used in architectural casting applications including facade connectors, curtain wall brackets, and decorative hardware where dimensional precision matters.</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/en/contact/" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:inline-flex;">Request specifications →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="final-cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Sourcing aluminium for construction projects?</h2>
      <p>Noel Murphy handles all European enquiries. Response within 24 hours.</p>
      <div class="final-cta-actions">
        <a href="/en/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Request a Quote</a>
        <a href="https://wa.me/353871187806" class="btn btn-secondary">WhatsApp</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
